More tertiary education students are expected back in class in a phased manner in the coming weeks. JOHANNESBURG - The Minister of Higher Education Blade Nzimande will brief the media on progress in the implementation of COVID-19 measures on Tuesday. Nzimande held a media briefing on 23 May in which he briefed the media on issues affecting NSFAS allowances, SETA’s stipends and the phased return of students and Higher Health. WATCH: SA tertiary education institutions to reopen in June The minister is expected to focus on post-school education and training institution readiness, implementation of Higher Health plans, electronic devices and data for students and student funding policy. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.